<subSubSection id="C30B26F86479FFE68BAE4A8EFD8911D3" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAE75736479FFE68BAE4A8EFECF1163" blockId="9.[151,445,726,789]" box="[151,298,762,789]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">
<figureCitation id="132A69F66479FFE68BAE4A8EFECF1163" box="[151,298,762,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–15" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[163,1419,191,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[151,1436,181,1857]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 8–15. Ulomyia iberica sp. nov.: 8 eyebridge; 9 antennal base; 10 antennal flagellomeres 12–14; 11 flagellomere 6 with ascoids; 12 wing; 13 patagium with scent organ; 14 styles, aedeagus and ventral bridge; 15 epandrium with appendages and hypoproct. Scale bars: Fig. 12—1 mm; Figs 8, 9, 10, 11, 13, 14, 15—0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488094" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488094/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Figures 8–15</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAE75736479FFE68BAE4B37FD8911D3" blockId="9.[151,1437,834,2014]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B965A9616479FFE68BAE4B37FEEE112A" bold="true" box="[151,267,834,860]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Diagnose.</emphasis>
An 
<taxonomicName id="4C110EF06479FFE68A034B36FE17112B" box="[314,498,835,861]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis id="B965A9616479FFE68A034B36FE7F112B" box="[314,410,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Ulomyia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
with eye bridge of six facet rows; antenna with all flagellomeres separate, first flagellomere with strong setae; thorax with bilobed patagia with an apical bulb; gonostyles longer than gonocoxites, ejaculatory apodeme as long as gonostyli.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
